summary: SummaryPro Brow Definer 1MM-Tip Brow Pencil by MAC, a pin-thin 24HR brow definer that delivers natural high definition, hair-like strokes with a water- and smudge-proof formula for 24 hour wear. Our finest brow definer featuring 14 shades with true colour payoff that serve up fuller-looking brows all day.
details: DetailsBenefitsLong-wearing, 24 hoursWaterproofSmudge-proof, color-true and non-fading, 24 hoursTransfer-resistantDual-ended 1mm precision tip and spoolie14 true-to-you shadesKey IngredientsUnique blend of carnauba wax, castor, argan & coconut oils: Help pigments glide on to resist tugging and breakageItem 2623821How To UseApply the eyebrow pencil using small, quick strokes in the direction of natural hair growth to fill in and shape for a naturally defined look.The 1mm precision tip mimics the look of natural hair.Blend pigment with the spoolie end for a seamless diffused finish.IngredientsHydrogenated Soybean Oil, Hydrogenated Coco-Glycerides, Zinc Stearate, Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil, Rhus Verniciflua Peel Wax, Copernicia Cerifera (Carnauba) Wax\ Copernicia Cerifera Cera \Cire De Carnauba, Caprylic/Capric Glycerides, Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil, Cocos Nucifera (Coconut) Oil, Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Tocopherol, [+/- Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491), Iron Oxides (CI 77492), Iron Oxides (CI 77499), Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140)]Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Too Little Product = No Thank You
reviews.comments: I miss the old eye brow pencil. There is NOT enough product to last you even 1 month! Its a rip off for the price. Do better MAC! Im a loyal patron since the 90s and this was my go-to every decade. Please bring back the old eye brow pencil!

reviews.headline: New pencil a real rip off
reviews.comments: Yes, please bring back the product you offered us before where it didn't RUn OUT IN 2 WEEKS, and razor thin, unlike the one previously offered us! How sad for the cunsumers!

reviews.headline: Cool
reviews.comments: Wish it last longer.

reviews.headline: First time
reviews.comments: Bought this yesterday, absolutely love it. Have tried so many other brands Anastasia, benefit, L'Or√©al, too many to name. This is by far my favorite. It is skinny, so you can use it right where you need it. It does not smudge and ball up. I wish I found it sooner. Do not know why it is not rated higher!

reviews.headline: Not buying again
reviews.comments: Easy to break the pencil

reviews.headline: Disappointed!
reviews.comments: I am a MAC lover and this is the first product that left me disappointed. The product breaks easily because of how thin it is. I've adjusted by twisting a tiny amount from the end of the pencil and working with it that way. I do like the color STUD.

reviews.headline: Disappointed
reviews.comments: This has been my go-to brow pencil for over a decade. I don't know if the formulation changed or what, but restocking years later, my brows were completely wiped out when I broke a sweat. I still love the tip size, but will have to figure out a fix.

reviews.headline: Shrink-flation! Where is the eyebrow STYLER?
reviews.comments:
They took the perfectly good MAC Eye Brow Styler  and packaged it into a much smaller size (1 mm-Tip) for the same price that the MAC Eyebrow Styler use to be. 

Now this product runs out much too quickly.

reviews.headline: Fantastic Fine Tip Brow Pencil
reviews.comments: I love this brow Pencil. Truly one of my favorites second only to the Kosas Brow Pop Nano.  Excellent for filling in or even creating brow hairs depending on how sparce your brow hairs are. I use the Benefit Brow Pencil for shaping  and this one and the Kosas for filling in space hairs. Love it. I have not experiencing any breaking with this one and I've re-ordered it at least 6 times at this point. It is nothing like the Huda one that would break at every tiny bit of pressure and use. Highly Recommend this one. I use Taupe and love the color and the formula that stays on all day.

reviews.headline: Worse Pencil Evee!
reviews.comments: The MAC eyebrow pencil was my go to for years to do my eyebrows. I purchased a new one two months ago where the packaging changed & all around the product is trash. Really olling the pencil up can only be gone about 10 times & the pencil is gone. The pencil keeps breaking when you put it to your. With the price we pay for a pencil that doesn't last, this was my last time purchasing this from MAC.

reviews.headline: Don't waste your money
reviews.comments: This eye brow pencil is simply too fragile. The slightest "force" and the tip breaks off, which means you won't have the product for very long. For the price, it just isn't worth it.

reviews.headline: 1 of my 3 favorite brow pencils
reviews.comments: I love the thin tip of this pencil, it helps me get fine hair like stokes on my fine brows for a natural full look. I don't love the price as I use one pencil a month with daily use.

reviews.headline: MY FAVORITE EYEBROW PENCIL
reviews.comments: this eyebrow pencil has been my HOLY GRAIL! as someone who battled cancer and lost her right eyebrow to it, ive struggled to find a pencil that looks natural. This pencil is perfect from the color range, to the tip size!! Those saying it breaks easily dont know you just need to use a light pressure because the tip is so fine! It makes the most realistic looking eyebrow hairs and helps me feel confident. please never discontinue this product!!! its my favorite.

reviews.headline: Kept breaking
reviews.comments: I loved it but every time I used it , it broke. It only lasted 2 weeks because of this. Maybe user error???

reviews.headline: Best brow pencil for me
reviews.comments: After letting my hair go gray, so salt and pepper now, I've tried so many different brands to find a not too brown not too gray coloring for my eyebrows. My Ulta hairstylist recommended this one and it is the best pencil I have ever used. It's  really creamy. So I guess a con is that it gets used quickly. Have to be very careful not to turn it up too much or it will break. A little goes a long way.

reviews.headline: Buying again
reviews.comments: If you want to have a good pencil for your eyebrow, definitely this is the one I'm using this almost one year it's it's really really good

reviews.headline: Way too thin
reviews.comments: The tip is way too thin and breaks off easily. I had been using this product for years.  Alot less product too, but the same price tag. Super disappointed with this one.

reviews.headline: Too thin
reviews.comments: Breaks too easily

reviews.headline: Too 5hin
reviews.comments: The pencil is so thin it easily breaks while applying.  For such an expensive item that is not ok

reviews.headline: Tried it, liked it buying again!
reviews.comments: I really like this MAC brow pencil. Found a great color to match.  I especially like the eye brow brush it helps with that blending process that looks more natural. I really like it because it stays on all day. I'm purchasing again todayüëçüèº

faceoff_positive.comments:
The MAC Pro Brow Definer is a game-changer for achieving perfectly sculpted brows. Its precise tip allows for effortless application, helping to define and shape brows with ease.

Compared to other brow products I've tried, the MAC Pro Brow Definer stands out for its precise application and long-lasting formula. While some other products may smudge or fade throughout the day, this one stays put, giving a polished look that lasts.

Some benefits of owning this product include:

1. Precise application:  The fine tip allows for precise and controlled application, helping to achieve defined brows effortlessly. 
2. Long-lasting formula: The long-wear formula ensures that brows stay in place all day without smudging or fading, making it ideal for busy days or special occasions.
3. Range of shades: With a variety of shades available, it's easy to find the perfect match for your brows, whether you prefer a natural look or something more bold.                                              I would definitely buy this product, as it has become a staple in my makeup routine. Its reliability and ease of use make it worth the investment.
I would absolutely recommend this product to my friends and family. Whether they're makeup enthusiasts or just looking for an easy way to enhance their brows, this product delivers exceptional results that are sure to impress.
faceoff_positive.headline: MAC Pro Brow Definer

faceoff_negative.comments:
I don't know why Mac decided to change this product?!?!  This was my go to product for my eyebrows.  I would draw in my eyebrows everyday using this pencil, or use it here and there when needed.  It was a PERFECT pencil.  I have blonde hair, shave my face, including my eyebrows.  I do have my eyebrows microbladed, shaded, etc‚Ä¶ However, I would still use the pencil in certain areas, the pencil colors were perfect, the pencil was perfect in width, and lasted a good amount of time!  When my eyebrows would lighten over time, I would use this product and this product alone to draw in my eyebrows completely.  Took a long time before it would run out!
Now they changed it;
The pencil now is so thin!  And since my eyebrows are due for micro blading, I was using my pencil much more, and it was only lasting me 2 WEEKS!  So FRUSTRATING!  Beyond ANNOYED!  Why companies change great products is beyond my comprehension!

I guess if you need a very small line, to fill something in, and don't use it often, then it's perfect for you!

If you use it a lot, don't bother! You will run out so fast, it's not even worth it!
And when I say thin, I mean a very thin line, that will also break very easy.
Maybe they think everyone has big bushy eyebrows now?!
I'll take the original product back now! And pray they do bring it back!

It took me so long to even find a good replacement, after testing out a million different products, I finally found a couple I love!  So, I guess eyebrow pencil is now off my list!
Sad
faceoff_negative.headline: Bring Back the Old One
